  <static seed="90" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring510.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{10t^{3}+90t}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>10t\mathopen{}\left(t^{2}+9\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We note that <m>10t</m> is common to both 
terms</p>
<p><m>{10t^{3}+90t}  =  {10t\mathopen{}\left(t^{2}+9\right)}</m></p>
<p>We can not factor the expression further, since the binomial is a sum of squares.</p>
</solution>
